HEADWORD: Bipyramidal
<hw>Bi`py*ram"i*dal</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>pyramidal</ets>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of two
pyramids placed base to base; having a pyramid at each of the
extremities of a prism, as in quartz crystals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biquadrate</ent>⟦br⟧
